                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary>Can drip irrigation work on any shaped or sized field?</summary>
                    <p>Yes. Drip irrigation is highly adaptable. Systems can be designed for irregular shapes, steep slopes, odd-sized plots, and large-scale operations alike. Your local DripSmart dealer will spec a layout specific to your land.</p>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary>Does water quality affect my drip system?</summary>
                    <p>Water quality matters, but it's fully manageable. DripSmart systems include filtration options and emitter designs rated for hard water, recycled water, and even dairy effluent — your dealer will match the spec to your source.</p>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary>Will drip irrigation change my fertilizer routine?</summary>
                    <p>Mostly for the better. Precision fertigation delivers nutrients directly to the root zone in smaller, more frequent doses — which typically reduces total fertilizer use by 20–40% while improving crop uptake efficiency.</p>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary>How long does installation take?</summary>
                    <p>It depends on the scale, but most farm installations are completed within a few days. Your certified DripSmart dealer handles installation and commissioning and will give you a timeline upfront.</p>
                </details>
